paragraphs.text:
%md
We are going to create a table that is partitioned using dynamic partitioning

~~~sql
CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE  movie_title_partition( 
                        tconst string,
                        titleType string,
                        primaryTitle string,
                        originalTitle string,
                        isAdult string,
                        endYear string,
                        runtimeMinutes string,
                        genres ARRAY<STRING>
                        ) 
PARTITIONED BY (startYear string)
ROW FORMAT DELIMITED 
FIELDS TERMINATED BY '\t' 
LOCATION '/warehouse/tablespace/external/hive/movie_title_partition/';

DESCRIBE FORMATTED movie_title_partition;

INSERT INTO TABLE movie_title_partition
PARTITION(startYear)
SELECT tconst,titleType,primaryTitle,originalTitle,isAdult,endYear,runtimeMinutes,genres,startYear
FROM movie_title_stage;


~~~

But first we need to drop the table if it already exists.

paragraphs.text:
%md
#### Important

Loading partition tables requires multiple selects through the data, which is time consuming.
Loading partition data is in effect a full table scan for the cardinality of the partition column

paragraphs.title: 15 - Execute a query on the partitioned movie title table. Find the  title in uppercase of all the  movies that are short genre and have a runtime over 60 minutes.
paragraphs.text:
%jdbc(hive_interactive)
SELECT upper(primarytitle) FROM movie_title_partition WHERE runtimeminutes>60 AND array_contains(genres, 'Short')

paragraphs.title: 16 - Delete all of the movie titles that have a start year of 1959? ( What happens?) Try to solve. Hint: Hive ACID
17 -  What's the total runtime minutes of  short titles in 2001?
paragraphs.text:
%jdbc(hive_interactive)
SELECT sum(runtimeminutes) FROM movie_title_partition WHERE array_contains(genres, 'Short')
